Our Project Overview
Cyber Shield: Spot the Phishing Scam is a fun and interactive cyber safety game where players learn how to identify phishing scams, fake emails, and suspicious links through quiz challenges and simple real-life scenarios. The game is designed to teach important online safety skills in an engaging and easy-to-understand way for young learners.

The main cyber safety topics covered in the game include phishing scams, fake emails, suspicious links, password safety, and online scam awareness. Players will practice identifying unsafe online behavior and learn how to protect their personal information while using the internet.

Our group selected this topic because phishing scams are very common and can affect children and teenagers who use the internet daily. Many young users may not recognize fake messages or dangerous links, so the game aims to improve awareness and help players make smart and safe online decisions.

The target audience for the game is students aged 10–12 years old, beginner internet users, and school learners who want to improve their understanding of online safety and cyber security basics.

There are still several questions the team plans to explore during development. These include deciding what rewards or points players should earn during gameplay, determining how many quiz questions each level should contain, and choosing the style of characters and background designs that will make the game more engaging and enjoyable for players.
