Day 1 Reflection (day-1-reflection.md)

On Day 1 of the Cyber Shield: Spot the Phishing Scam project, our group completed several important tasks. We formed the group, discussed different cyber safety topics, selected our final game idea, and created the initial storyboard and game concept to guide the development of the project.

What went well was our teamwork and communication. Everyone actively shared their ideas, and we were able to agree on the game topic quickly without major conflicts. This helped us stay focused and move forward efficiently.

The main difficulty we faced was choosing the best game design and organising all our ideas into a simple and clear storyboard. It was challenging to keep everything structured in an easy-to-understand way.

For improvement, we need better time management, clearer task distribution, and more detailed planning of the game screens to avoid confusion later in the project.

For Day 2, our next steps are to create quiz questions, improve the storyboard, design game characters, and start building the game layout and structure.
